--------------------------------------------------------------
MEFISTO software        English Version            May 2011
--------------------------------------------------------------
NEWS:
MESHER
- Option 19 of surfaces: a TRIANGULER by adding of
  the barycentre of triangles with same data input as 9;
- Option 26 of 2D or 3D surfaces: a MODIFIER of a mesh of
  triangles or quadrangles by mouse clicks
- Option 38 of surfaces to show into a rectangle defined by
  2 clicks the triangles or quadrangles to extract
- Option 39 subdivide any triangle or quadrangle of the
  initial mesh into 4 sub elements of same type
- Addition of MULTI-MATERIALS VOLUMES(one materiau=one volume)
  An union of several volumes is a MULTI-MATERIALS VOLUME.
  A type 9 volume with several type 8 volumes is a 
  MULTI-MATERIALS VOLUME.
  The surfaces, interfaces between 2 materials are drawn.
- Volume 19 a TETRAHEDRIZER by adding of the barycentre
  of triangles with same data input as volume 9;
- Volume 16 a generator of pentahedra or hexahedra from the
  triangles or quadrangles of a surface by displacement along
  the normal vector at every vertex
- Volume 31 the tetrahedrization cuts the pyramida (from
  volume 15), the pentahedra and the hexahedra.
  If the volume is MULTI-MATERIALS, the materials which
  constitute it, are tetrahedrized and their previous meshes
  with pyramids, pentahedra, hexahedra are replaced.
  This replacement permits the compatibility of triangles
  on the interfaces, the limit of 2 materials.
- Volume 39 subdivide any tetrahedron into 8 sub-tetra
  any pentahedron into 8 sub-penta, any hexahedron into 8
  sub-hexa and pyramida into 6 sub-pyra and 4 sub-tetra
- Volume 48 imposes the 3 coordinates of the given point to
  the nearest vertex of the mesh
- Volume 51 an union of volumes into one multi-material volume
- Volume 53 a multi-material volume, union of volumes, is cut
  as many separated mono-material volumes
- Volume 54 a multi-material volume, union of volumes, becomes
  only one mono-material volume
- 1d OBJECT as several interval (1 per material) with 
  2 boundary POINTS, extremities of the object, support of
  future boundary conditions
HEATER:
- Computation of integral of solution**expo on the object
- Computation of steady or not heat transfer on 1d object
  with graphics of temperature, gradient, flux and error
- Display of gradients at quadrature formula points
- Display of fluxes at interface points between FE
- Drawing of the solutions at all steps of time
ELASTICER:
- Visualization of eigenmodes movements
FLUIDER
- Solution of the steady or unsteady STOKES problem,
  unsteady NAVIER-STOKES problem for an incompressible
  2D or 3D fluid by Taylor-Hood or Brezzi-Fortin finite
  elements with a skyline storage and CROUT factorization.
- Solution of unsteady NAVIER-STOKES problem by fractional
  steps by skyline Cholesky factorization or conjugate gradient
  => lower size of used memory
- Drawing of particles moving in a flow
- Drawing of the 2d stream function
- Drawing of the velocity norm inside the flow
- Drawing of the pressure on some surfaces of the fluid
- Drawing of the solutions at all steps of time
- A User's Manual of Mefisto-FLUIDER is loadable
